quran[25]{c,v,t}:
  55,1,The Compassionate
  55,2,taught the Quran
  55,3,created man
  55,4,taught him speech
  55,5,The sun and the moon are upon a reckoning
  55,6,And the stars and the trees prostrate
  55,7,Heaven He has raised and the Balance He has set
  55,8,that you transgress not in the balance
  55,9,So set right the weight and fall not short in the balance
  55,10,The earth has He laid down for creatures
  55,11,Therein are fruit and date palms bearing sheaths
  55,12,husked grains and fragrant herbs
  55,13,So which of your Lord’s boons do you two deny
  55,14,"He created man from dried clay, like earthen vessels"
  55,15,and He created jinn from smokeless fire
  55,16,So which of your Lord’s boons do you two deny
  55,17,Lord of the two easts and Lord of the two wests
  55,18,So which of your Lord’s boons do you two deny
  55,19,"He mixed the two seas, such that they meet one another"
  55,20,Between them lies a barrier that they transgress not
  55,21,So which of your Lord’s boons do you two deny
  55,22,From them come forth pearls and coral stones
  55,23,So which of your Lord’s boons do you two deny
  55,24,His are the ships towering aloft upon the sea like standards
  55,25,So which of your Lord’s boons do you two deny